title: God's Country Mountain Bike Classic
description: Round # 1 of the Unified Federation of Dirt season comes to Lawrence Kansas on March 24, 2012.  Classic cross country racing returns to the Lawrence River Trails for a fun day of racing.
course: The God\'s Country Mountain Bike Classic will be held on the Lawrence River Trails    The course consist of flowing single track along the Kaw River.  A great course that is fun for all ability levels.
registration:
Standard Unified Federation of Dirt classes. 
Kids race free
$15.00 for Juniors 
$25.00 for Marathon, Cat 2 & Cat 3 classes
$30.00 for Cat 1 classes
notes: Limited parking at trail head.  Please visit http://www.fattireduathlon.com for event updates.
directions: From Kansas City, take I-70 West to the first Lawrence exit.  Go South on Massachusetts until you go under a big rail-road trestle then turn left onto Elm. Keep going to 8th Street then turn right.  Continue over the Levee and Park.

title: Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey
description: Big time MTB racing returns to the Midwest with the 4th Annual Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey.  Come enjoy some of the sweetest trails in the Midwest.  Party with your friends and just have a grand old time riding your bike.  Your choice, 3 or 6 hours of fun.
course: The trails of Clinton Lake North Shore are again featured in this years event. A good combination of smooth flowing trails, technical rocky climbs/descents, creek crossings and double track.  Expect the course to be about 10 miles long this year.
notes:
Field limit is 300
$4.20 per car fee must be paid at the Park entrance. 
Camping is available onsite at Clinton State Park.
directions: From I-70, take exit #197 (Lecompton exit).  Take Hwy 10 south to the Clinton Parkway exit (3rd exit after exiting I-70). Turn right at the bottom of the exit ramp, take another right and the park will be on the left.  Take the second left which is 1415 Road.  Follow the long drive to the park permit fee office.  Continue on past Campground #1 to the start of the Bone Bender which will again be held at the Swim Beach area.  Signs will be posted.

title: MMCT Salina 2 Day
description: Salina 2 Day is a Road Race on Saturday morning and Crit Sunday morning in Salina KS.
course: The Crit is flat and fast in historic downtown Salina.  The RR is http://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/92091267/?new_route=1.
registration: Online registration to include (electronically signed) waiver is highly suggested to avoid lines.  Register online at https://www.usacycling.org/myusac/index.php?pagename=registration&eventid=2039&year=2012.  Day of  Sunday crit registration will be in downtown Salina at Sante Fe Street and Ash Street.  Day of registration Saturday for the Road Race will be at the Vortex Building at 1725 Vortex Avenue Salina, KS. On site registration opens at 7:30 am each day and will close at 8:30 for the RR. Sunday and 30 minutes prior to each crit on Sunday.  Contact John Fairbanks at johnarlenef@att.net for more information.
notes: We will be awarding the top finisher in both races an award based on scoring with a 1st place finisher receiving 10 pts for 1ST 9 for 2ND etc.  The 2 races will be added together and award for 1st only.  This is a KBAR pts event with free entry to 2011 KBAR winners. Race Director may combine fields with less than 10 entries.  All USAC rules apply.  CPSC approved helmets must be worn at all times on a moving bike.  Valid USAC license required and must be presented at registration.  Annual and One Day licenses available for purchase at registration.  Bonus for 50+ Men and Women and 60+ Women is 50/35/25/15.  40+ Men and 50+ Men are competing for field purse with 50+ Men also receiving bonus for placing in their age group.  40+, 50+ and 60+ Women are competing for field purse with 50+ Women and 60+ Women also receiving bonus for placing in their age group.
directions: Crit Registration at Sante Fe and Ash and RR at Vortex Building.  Special rate at Salina Ramada of $69 if made by May 1st and Salina Bike Races are mentioned.
